In the latest attack against Pakistan's Hazara Shia minority, a bomb ripped
through a busy market in the southwestern city of Quetta in Pakistan on
February 16, [claiming as many as 63
lives](http://tribune.com.pk/story/508261/blast-on-kirani-road-in-quetta/) and
injuring at least 180 others, including many women and children.

The bombing occurred in Hazara Town, a territory home to the [Hazara community
of Shia
Muslims](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hazara_people#Hazaras_in_Pakistan), who
were also the target of an [attack last month that left 96 people
dead.](http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2013/01/2013117124512947691.html)
In that incident, a suicide bomber detonated his explosives inside a billiard
parlor, killing several people. Shortly afterward, as people rushed to help
the victims, a car bomb outside the parlor went off.

The banned militant organization, [Lashkar-e-Jhangvi
](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lashkar-e-Jhangvi)(LeJ), which allegedly has
[ties to Pakistan's intelligence
agency](http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2013%5C02%5C16%5Cstory_16-2-2013_pg3_4),
has [claimed ](http://uk.reuters.com/article/2013/02/16/uk-pakistan-violence-
shiites-idUKBRE91F02O20130216)responsibility for [the
bombings](http://www.hazara.net/downloads/pakistan/lej-
statement_alamdar_road_blast_jan102013.html).

As the sectarian violence against Pakistan's Hazaras continue unabated, many
across the country have accused the government of deadly inaction, demanding
that authorities move off the sidelines and step in to halt the mass killings.

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2013/02/Snapshot_131-375x259.jpeg)](http://www.facebook.com/Mechidtv/posts/427927643956485)

Screenshot of video recorded and published by a witness at the blast scene.

[Ali Dayan Hasan](https://twitter.com/AliDayan), the Human Rights Watch
director for Pakistan, [criticized the government's
absence](https://twitter.com/AliDayan/status/302805387407667200) on Twitter:

> [@AliDayan:](https://twitter.com/AliDayan/status/302805387407667200) What
> action has been taken since the last massacre of the
> [#Hazara](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Hazara&src=hash) in January to
> hold the LeJ accountable? Nothing.
> [#Balochistan](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Balochistan&src=hash)

Human Rights Watch [noted](http://www.hrw.org/news/2013/02/01/pakistan-abuses-
impunity-erode-rights) in its [World Report 2013](http://www.hrw.org/world-
report/2013) that the LeJ has ties to the Pakistani Inter-Services
Intelligence (ISI) and other intelligence services, writing that “Pakistan’s
government has failed to act against abuses by the security and intelligence
agencies, which continued to allow extremist groups to attack religious
minorities.” Hasan also
[asked](https://twitter.com/AliDayan/status/302800760658358272):

> If [#Pakistan](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pakistan&src=hash)‘s security
> agencies are neither incompetent nor complicit in the killing of
> [#Hazara](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Hazara&src=hash) Shias, why do
> they continue to die.

[Arif Hussain Hazara](https://twitter.com/Arif_Hazara) warned that inaction
would have tragic consequences:

> [@Arif_Hazara](https://twitter.com/Arif_Hazara/status/302802685160202240):
> [#HazaraTownBalst](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23HazaraTownBalst&src=hash)
> not the first, will not be the last
> unless[#ActionAgainstLeJ](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23ActionAgainstLeJ&src=hash)
> is being taken, they r strategic poison not asset. [~~  
> ~~](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23ForGodSake&src=hash)

[![People gather near the dead bodies of victims, who were gunned down by
unidentified armed men at the Scrap Market on Sarki Road in a target killing.
Quetta, Pakistan. 16th October 2012  Image by PPPIimages. Copyright
Demotix](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
